   <h1>The Troll&#39;s Bane Chronicle</h1>

   <h2>The fifth year of the new era: February</h2>

<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 2nd, the second election of the Triumvirate commences. The candidates are Cliu Beothach and Gannon.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 3rd, an unknown person puts up a parchment from Johann Endan's feather, which contains his last words.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 3rd, Ules Felko reports of yet more attacks led by the Bloodskulls against Troll's Bane.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 5th, an assassin offers his services for poor payment.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 5th, Durin Goldtooth warns of cutting too many trees in the southern forest, because many trolls appeared again.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 7th, Gwynnether von Glanwen reports that Johann Endan has killed himself and that she executed Nikagor Fyrstyn, after both had abducted John Irenicus.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 8th, the Order of the Grey Light recruits new members.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 13th, there is gossip in the town about a group called "Havoc", spies and shadowguards who seek to spread to Troll's Bane. The rumors weaken quickly, however.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 15th, Marius Eisenhauer warns of rotworm attacks near the coal mine.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 16th, Drex Thaendrak complains about some rotting bones that are spread out over the market plaza, and demands from the Triumvirate and the Town Guard to dispose of them.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 18th, Cliu Beothach announces his marriage with Irania.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 18th, Marius Eisenhauer demands for his belongings to be returned from Shil Shaah Shenoss, who had attacked him during some forestry work in the southern forest.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 19th, the assassin demands his staff to be returned to him, lest he murder an innocent for every next day that passes. He was however captured later and locked away in the dungeon of the Grey Retreat.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 21st, the second election of the Triumvirate ends. The winner is Gannon, who thereby takes up his job as the third member of the council.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 21st, Lennier appeals the citizens of Troll's Bane to unite and take concerted action against the Bloodskulls, after new incidents occurred again.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 21st, Jaques Pilar offers his services as an artist. He gets his first assignment from the Bloodskull Gorge, who wants a nude portrait.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 21st, the Bloodskull Gorge announces that he, Krubba, and Grutok, together abducted Eliza and now demand a ransom.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 21st, the Guild "Trollsbanes Herbests, Ink makers, Entertainers, and Farmers" is founded. It seems to develop quickly, although the guild does not make any public appearance.</p>
<p>In the year 5 of the new era on February the 27th, Varshikar founds the "Varshikar Magery Academy", which shall serve as an official authority to educate druids and mages for Varshikar.</p>

